[3] UK (England)
Date: Thu 7 Jun 2012
Source: The Argus [edited]
http://www.theargus.co.uk/news/9748448.Fresh_cases_of_measles_at_Lewes_school/


Fresh cases of measles at Lewes school
--------------------------------------
Fresh cases of measles have been reported at a school. Priory School in Mountfield Road, Lewes, has issued a warning to parents that several more pupils have been diagnosed as having contracted the disease. Staff have written to parents warning them that measles spreads easily and poses a particular danger to young babies, pregnant women, and the vulnerable. The letter continues: "If your child has measles please keep them away from school and away from other people for 4 days after the day the rash starts. This is so they do not pass the disease to others."

Schools in Lewes, Brighton, Hove, Crawley, and Heathfield have all reported outbreaks of measles this year.

