[10] Australia (Queensland)
Date: Fri 6 Jun 2012
Source: TopNews United States [edited]
http://topnews.us/content/248757-queensland-health-issues-warning-after-case-measles-surfaces


Queensland Health issues warning after a case of measles surfaces
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Measles is spread through respiration on contact with fluids from an infected person's nose and mouth, either directly or through aerosol transmission. It is highly contagious and 90 per cent of the people without immunity sharing living space with an infected person can catch it. There has been an alert issued by Queensland Health on measles. It has also urged the general population to be wary of the symptoms of the measles virus. An asymptomatic incubation period occurs 9 to 12 days from initial exposure and infectivity lasts from 2 to 4 days prior, until 2 to 5 days following the onset of the rash. Queensland Health has urged people to be alert for symptoms of the measles virus. According to Dr Brad McCall, there has been a confirmed case of measles, who visited a south west shopping centre and a cafe on 3 Jun 2012 and who also travelled on the Beenleigh-Ferny Grove rail service. Queensland Health is now urging the people who were at these places during that time to be alert for the symptoms of measles. It is highly likely that any person who was in close contact with the infected person might also have caught the virus.

